01:39:58.800 --> 01:40:04.310
of George III's madness but
I was wondering of this sheds

01:40:04.310 --> 01:40:06.600
in any new light on how it--

01:40:06.600 --> 01:40:14.600
or its incipient stages may
have affected policy in Britain.

01:40:14.600 --> 01:40:18.840
&gt;&gt; Andrew O'Shaughnessy: He
had about sickness at the time

01:40:18.840 --> 01:40:23.720
of [inaudible] in the 1765,
which went on for months.

01:40:23.720 --> 01:40:27.580
So that was actually the
first intimation of it.

01:40:27.580 --> 01:40:31.990
But there's no evidence that
he was sick during the American

01:40:31.990 --> 01:40:33.440
Revolution itself.

01:40:33.440 --> 01:40:35.550
It was really on the eve
of the French Revolution

01:40:35.550 --> 01:40:40.310
that he had the first
sustained belt that was

01:40:40.310 --> 01:40:46.330
in fact the subject to the movie
"The Madness of King George".

01:40:46.330 --> 01:40:49.100
The thinking seems
to be changing.

01:40:49.100 --> 01:40:54.210
For decades, they thought
that this was porphyria.

01:40:54.210 --> 01:40:58.300
It's a mother-son
team of psychiatrists.

01:40:58.300 --> 01:41:02.100
And I thought that they've
made quite a conclusive case

01:41:02.100 --> 01:41:06.560
because there's a giveaway
characteristic of porphyria

01:41:06.560 --> 01:41:10.230
which is a blood disease
caused often by intermarriage,

01:41:10.230 --> 01:41:16.400
very like hemophilia but it's
kind of purple-colored urine.

01:41:16.400 --> 01:41:22.750
And so-- And one of the
doctors constantly alluded

01:41:22.750 --> 01:41:28.830
to urine color and we've
got incredible archives

01:41:28.830 --> 01:41:32.340
of the doctor's reports.

01:41:32.340 --> 01:41:36.340
But it seems that
it's changing again.

01:41:36.340 --> 01:41:42.280
I've actually seen this in
the BBC, an academic article

01:41:42.280 --> 01:41:47.410
that they're going back to
thinking that he was bipolar

01:41:47.410 --> 01:41:50.390
and that would make
a difference.

01:41:50.390 --> 01:41:55.430
But-- And there's nothing
of the characteristics

01:41:55.430 --> 01:42:01.260
of the later madness of then
in 1765 and then again 1789.

